Title: Docker Image Based Web Application

Objective
To create and deploy a web application using Docker.

Tools Used
- Docker
- Python
- Flask

Step 1: Create Web Application
- Created a Python Flask application (app.py).
- The app displays a simple message on the browser.

Source Code (app.py)
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return "Hello, this is my Dockerized Web App!"

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)

Step 2: Create Requirements File
requirements.txt
flask

Step 3: Create Dockerfile
- Used Python base image.
- Installed dependencies.
- Copied project files.
- Defined startup command.

Dockerfile
FROM python:3.10
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
CMD ["python", "app.py"]

Step 4: Build Docker Image
Command used:
docker build -t my-web-app .

Step 5: Run Docker Container
Command used:
docker run -p 5000:5000 my-web-app

Step 6: Output
- The application runs on:
http://localhost:5000

- Output:
Hello, this is my Dockerized Web App!

Conclusion
Successfully created and deployed a Docker-based web application.

Github repo here: https://github.com/KshKnsl/docker-demo